<p>Let's say that you have the following code:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;input name="my-input' id="my-input-id" /&gt; &lt;label for="my-input-id"&gt; </code></pre>  <p>There's a click event attached to the label, like so:</p>  <pre><code>$("label[for='my-input-id']").click( function() {     var myLabel = $(this); } </code></pre>  <p>What's the easiest/simplest way to get a jQuery object of the input via the myLabel jQuery object?</p>